President Trump welcomes the 2018 NASCAR Cup Series Champion, Joey Logano, and Team Penske to the White House. He congratulates Logano and the team on their victory and praises their accomplishments. The President also acknowledges the presence of other political figures and members of Congress at the event. He commends NASCAR for being a celebration of the American spirit and expresses his admiration for the skill and courage of the drivers. Roger Penske, Chairman of Penske Corporation, thanks the President for his support of the military and first responders. Logano speaks about the honor of being at the White House and expresses gratitude for the opportunity to live his dream in a great country. He presents the President with a helmet and a trophy from the championship season. The President thanks him and offers to give the crew a tour of the Lincoln Bedroom.